VALUES (334, 'Meadows Row Video Exercise Guide', 'Upper Back', 'Strength', 'Landmine', 'Compound', 'Pull (Unilateral)',
        'Beginner', 'Abs, Biceps, Lats, Lower Back, Shoulders', 'The meadows row is a unilateral landmine exercise used to target the muscles of the back. The meadows row also challenges one’s grip and indirectly targets the muscles of the bicep.
